items.summary: BWB Monthly Sunday rides, Women only
items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Biking with Baddies Monthly Sunday rides, Women only Instagram, Website.

Last Sunday of every month. 2:00 PM 

Start: Logan Park 690 13th Ave NE

Who is this for: Women only

“All levels welcomed, no one left behind. Always refer to the website for updates. Come out with your bike and make new friends. There may be people you know, and/or folks that might want to get to know you on this ride. Even if that’s not the goal, come outside to cycle with us in nature.”
items.location: Logan Park, Minneapolis, MN, USA

items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Wedge Live Emergency Bike Ride. Event page.

When: Every Sunday at 7pm. Roll at 7:30pm. Aug 24, 2025, Aug 31, 2025

Start: Mueller Park (Colfax and W 25th St)

Distance: ?. Pace: Conversational, likely 8-12 mph.

What is an emergency bike ride? It's an immediate, systematic, coordinated response among partners at all levels, to the community's need for more bike rides.

Who can participate? Anyone of any skill level who feels an urgent need to ride your bike at a leisurely conversational pace in a group setting.

Are scooters ok? Yes.

items.description:
Group ride (drop) Tuesday Night Rides. Facebook.

When: Tuesdays. Meet at 5:45 pm, roll at 6:00 pm. Aug 19, 2025, Aug 26, 2025

Start and Finish: HeadFlyer Brewing

Two pace groups. Spicy: 14-16 mph pace for 20-25 miles Mild: 11-13 mph pace for 15-20 miles.

Routes published on Monday in the FB group. Rides feature a mid-ride restaurant stop and have the option to end back at Headflyer for a pint. There are no sweeps, so this can be a drop ride. Bring lights, lock, helmet, flat-fixing kit, anything you need to get yourself home.
items.location: HeadFlyer Brewing, 861 E Hennepin Ave #100, Minneapolis, MN 55414, USA

items.description:
Race (CX) Versus cross III. Instagram

When: Sunday Oct 19, 2025. 9am-4pm

Where: Huset Park, Columbia Heights. 

Cost: TBA (reg opens Sept 1), but typically $25-35/race, with a $10 “citizen” race for people new to the sport.

The best cyclocross race in Minnesota is back for its third year! Come race and spectate at Huset Park in Columbia Heights. Get some food from @kramarczuks and @nordicdogs612, chat all things bike fit, strength programming and PT with @go_physio_mn, and hang with our other vendors and sponsors! There will be a kids race and face painting—stick around for our signature Tracklocross race and raffle at the end of the day! Registration Opens September 1—stay tuned!
items.location: Huset Park, 3965 Jefferson St NE, Columbia Heights, MN 55421, USA

items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Angry Catfish Wednesday social ride. Instagram. Discord. Website.

When: Wednesday Oct 1, 2025 rolling at 6:00 pm. First Wednesday of each month during cold weather months.

Start: Angry Catfish Bicycle Finish: Venn Brewing Company

Distance: ~15 miles. Pace: 12-13 mph.

Bring lights, dress for the weather. Led by: Alex & Adam

Some additional considerations as weather gets colder:
- Dress for the weather, we will ride even when the temperature gets real low. Layers, pogies, and toe warmers are your friends. Ask friends how they layer, experiment and enjoy the thrill of winter riding.
- Ride based on your comfort level - rides will be in the dark and can be icy/snowy. Studded and/or fat tires encouraged in the depths of winter. Lights required.

Led by: Alex & Adam.

See Discord link for ride updates.
items.location: Angry Catfish Bicycle, 2900 E 42nd St, Minneapolis, MN 55406, USA

Bringing the whole community together for a ride you don’t want to miss! Expect music, a photobooth, a videographer to capture the vibes, and a pit stop at Surly Brewing. This will be a casual ride. Think sexy pace, chill pace, a ride where you can feel the laughs. We will have Marshall’s and Mechanics on hand for safety. Pull up on whatever bike you have! Road bike, BMX bike, gravel, cruiser, whatever you got on two wheels hell even tricycles are welcomed.

items.description:
Race (alleycat) La Bicicleta Viviente fundraiser alleycat. Instagram. Reg form.

When: Sunday Oct 12, 2025 12:30 PM. Race begins at 1 pm. 

Start: Venture Bikes Midtown.

Cost: Sliding scale $15-$25 (cash or venmo)

La Bicicleta Viviente is a choose-your-own-adventure alleycat celebrating life, friendship and movement—raising funds for Festival de las Calaveras. Expect pan dulce stops, cumbia beats, and a little friendly chaos. Come roll with us and make the city a living altar. Live music from: Sunsets Over Flowers, Manny, and We ♥️ Fiesta. Winners receive prizes from local latino artists and more. 

Categories: Open, WTF/NB, DFL, Best Costume.

If racing isn’t your thing: take the guided route and experience the alleycat at party pace.

Bring: helmet, lights, lock, phone, water.

Safety: obey traffic laws, ride predictably, respect neighbors.

Costume note: I think this goes without saying, culture is not your costume please do not appropriate.
items.location: Venture Bikes Midtown, 2834 10th Ave S, Minneapolis, MN 55407, USA

items.description:
Group ride (no-drop) Behind Bars FTW Wood-Rill ride. Instagram.

When: Saturday Oct 11, 2025 11:00 AM

Start: Behind Bars Bicycle Shop. 

Distance: 30 miles round trip. Pace: ?, likely 12-15 mph. 

Who’s this for: FTW (anyone but cis-men). See this resource from Grease Rag defining FTW.

Join @behindbarsbicycleshop ambassador Veronica @duck.emoji on Saturday October 11th at 11am for a ~30 mile round trip for FTW (no cis-men!) riders to explore and hike Wood-Rill SNA! The park is a quiet big woods forest conveniently located on the Luce Line. The area is full of gorgeous trees over 200 years old, mushrooms, tree frogs (!) And a changing fall scenery.

The trails are overgrown at some points so long socks/pants are recommended, and a pair of shoes for hiking!
